Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc’s (LON:RBS) “Hold” Rating Reiterated at Shore Capital

					Posted by Kim Johansen on Jul 28th, 2017 // No Comments 




Shore Capital reaffirmed their hold rating on shares of Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc (LON:RBS)  in a research note released on Thursday, July 13th.
Several other research firms have also issued reports on RBS. Natixis raised their price target on Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc from GBX 289 ($3.76) to GBX 303 ($3.95) and gave the stock a buy rating in a research report on Friday, May 5th. Macquarie lifted their price objective on Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc from GBX 270 ($3.52) to GBX 290 ($3.78) and gave the company an outperform rating in a research note on Friday, May 5th. J P Morgan Chase & Co  reiterated a neutral rating and set a GBX 230 ($3.00) price objective on shares of Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc in a research note on Tuesday, May 2nd. Barclays PLC lifted their price objective on Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc from GBX 250 ($3.26) to GBX 260 ($3.39) and gave the company an equal weight rating in a research note on Tuesday, May 2nd. Finally, Citigroup Inc. boosted their price target on Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc from GBX 190 ($2.48) to GBX 220 ($2.87) and gave the stock a sell rating in a research note on Tuesday, May 2nd. Six equities research analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, ten have issued  a hold rating and three have assigned  a buy rating to the company. The company currently has a consensus rating of Hold and a consensus price target of GBX 244.74 ($3.19).


 Get Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc alerts:



Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc (RBS) opened at 250.20 on Thursday. The stock’s market cap is GBX 29.56 billion. Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc has a 1-year low of GBX 168.20 and a 1-year high of GBX 271.00. The firm’s 50-day moving average is GBX 251.84 and its 200-day moving average is GBX 244.90. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: This story was  reported by Markets Daily and is owned by of Markets Daily. If you are accessing this story on another domain, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of international trademark & copyright legislation. The original version of this story can be viewed at https://www.themarketsdaily.com/2017/07/28/royal-bank-of-scotland-group-plcs-lonrbs-hold-rating-reiterated-at-shore-capital-updated.html. 




In other Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc news, insider Ross McEwan purchased 187,674 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction on Friday, May 12th. The stock was acquired at an average price of GBX 266 ($3.47) per share, for a total transaction of £499,212.84 ($650,355.45). 
About Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc
The Royal Bank of Scotland Group plc (RBS) is a banking and financial services company. The Company provides a range of products and services to personal, commercial, corporate and institutional customers, through its subsidiaries, The Royal Bank of Scotland plc and National Westminster Bank Plc (NatWest), as well as through other brands, including Ulster Bank and Coutts.







